{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbb8fafa2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1862o"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1862o"},"text":"§ 1862o.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Postdoctoral research fellows","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbb8fafa3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1862o/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Mentoring","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Director shall require that all grant applications that include funding to support postdoctoral and graduate student researchers include a description of the mentoring activities that will be provided for such individuals, and shall ensure that this part of the application is evaluated under the Foundation’s broader impacts merit review criterion. The requirement may be satisfied by providing such individuals with access to mentors, including individuals not listed on the award. Mentoring activities may include career counseling, training in preparing grant applications, guidance on ways to improve teaching skills, and training in research ethics.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbb8fafa4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1862o/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Reports","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Director shall require that annual reports and the final report for research grants that include funding to support postdoctoral researchers include a description of the mentoring activities provided to such researchers.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbb8fafa5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/69/tVII/s7008"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–69, title VII, § 7008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-08-09"},"text":"Aug. 9, 2007","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/121/680"},"text":"121 Stat. 680","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/167/dB/tIII/s10313/a/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–167, div. B, title III, § 10313(a)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-08-09"},"text":"Aug. 9, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/1522"},"text":"136 Stat. 1522","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbb8fafa6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbb8fafa7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idbb8fafa8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the America COMPETES Act, also known as the America Creating Opportunities to Meaningfully Promote Excellence in Technology, Education, and Science Act, and not as part of the National Science Foundation Act of 1950 which comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idbb8fafa9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2022—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/167"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–167","children":[],"tail":" inserted “and graduate student” after “postdoctoral” and “The requirement may be satisfied by providing such individuals with access to mentors, including individuals not listed on the award.” after “review criterion.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idbb8fafaa-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idbb8fafab-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Reaffirmation of the Merit-Review Process of the National Science Foundation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/69/tVII/s7003"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–69, title VII, § 7003","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-08-09"},"text":"Aug. 9, 2007","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/121/679"},"text":"121 Stat. 679","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/110/69/tVII/s7003"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"“Nothing in this title [enacting this section and sections 1862n–1a and 1862","children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"o","children":[],"tail":"–1 to 1862"},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"o","children":[],"tail":"–15 of this title, amending sections 1862i, 1862"},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":", 1862n, 1862n–1, 1862n–2, 1862n–5, 1863, 1870, and 1881a of this title, sections 5503 and 5511 of Title 15, Commerce and Trade, and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s3801"},"text":"section 3801 of Title 31","children":[],"tail":", Money and Finance, enacting provisions set out as notes under this section and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1862n–2"},"text":"section 1862n–2 of this title","children":[],"tail":", and amending provisions set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s1113"},"text":"section 1113 of Title 31","children":[],"tail":"] or title I [enacting sections 6603, 6619, and 6620 of this title and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s3718"},"text":"section 3718 of Title 15","children":[],"tail":" and amending "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s3711"},"text":"section 3711 of Title 15","children":[],"tail":"], or the amendments made by this title or title I, shall be interpreted to require or recommend that the Foundation—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" alter or modify its merit-review system or peer-review process; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" exclude the awarding of any proposal by means of the merit-review or peer-review process.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idbb8fafac-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Curricula","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/69/tVII/s7005"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–69, title VII, § 7005","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-08-09"},"text":"Aug. 9, 2007","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/121/679"}